01:00:01.975 --> 01:00:03.305
is all you've got on you,
then there's no problem.

1004
01:00:03.434 --> 01:00:05.481
If you'd just like to come this way
to the manager's office.

1005
01:00:05.561 --> 01:00:06.482
No, I'm not going to the manager's office.

1006
01:00:06.562 --> 01:00:08.772
You just stood there and watched
her serve me, I've got a receipt.

1007
01:00:08.898 --> 01:00:10.398
I can lock the door and call the police.

1008
01:00:10.525 --> 01:00:12.395
You're talking about locking the
door and calling the police.

1009
01:00:12.527 --> 01:00:14.027
Would you like to come with me
to the manager's office?

1010
01:00:14.153 --> 01:00:15.573
No, because I've just, you've
just watched me...

1011
01:00:16.114 --> 01:00:17.324
Okay, and we'll sort that out.

1012
01:00:17.448 --> 01:00:19.448
Okay, and if everything
on the receipt's in your bags,

1013
01:00:19.575 --> 01:00:21.195
- then there's no problem.
- You don't need to shout at me.

1014
01:00:21.327 --> 01:00:22.747
Okay, if you'd like to come this way.

1015
01:00:24.038 --> 01:00:25.708
She's just, you've just stood
there and watched it...

1016
01:00:25.832 --> 01:00:28.082
- Okay, then we'll sort it out.
- ...and serve me with, didn't you?

1017
01:00:28.209 --> 01:00:29.589
And she's given me a receipt.

1018
01:00:29.794 --> 01:00:30.844
Just this way.

1019
01:00:49.480 --> 01:00:51.440
Ivan, I'll take it from here.

1020
01:00:52.984 --> 01:00:54.404
What's your name, love?

1021
01:00:54.819 --> 01:00:56.489
- Katie.
- Katie?

1022
01:00:56.612 --> 01:00:58.742
- Katie Morgan.
- Katie Morgan.

1023
01:00:59.157 --> 01:01:00.277
I'm really sorry.

1024
01:01:00.616 --> 01:01:03.076
I haven't done anything like this before.
I've paid for these.

1025
01:01:07.165 --> 01:01:08.745
What are you gonna do?

1026
01:01:11.210 --> 01:01:12.250
Katie.

1027
01:01:13.880 --> 01:01:15.470
It's between me and you...

1028
01:01:16.674 --> 01:01:18.974
It's got nowt to do with the store.
All right?

1029
01:01:20.636 --> 01:01:21.966
They're paid for.

1030
01:01:26.434 --> 01:01:27.854
Get yoursel' away.

1031
01:01:32.648 --> 01:01:33.858
Thank you.

1032
01:01:48.664 --> 01:01:50.628
Hey, hang on a second. Hey, hang on...

1033
01:01:50.708 --> 01:01:53.088
I'm sorry about that, I am.

1034
01:01:53.669 --> 01:01:54.999
Can I get a quiet word?

1035
01:01:56.130 --> 01:02:00.340
Look, if you're in trouble and you
need money, I can help, okay?

1036
01:02:01.469 --> 01:02:03.349
Look, a nice girl like you,
I can definitely help.

1037
01:02:04.680 --> 01:02:07.100
That's my number. My name's Ivan, okay?

1038
01:02:11.687 --> 01:02:13.107
Ring me any time, all right?

1039
01:02:13.481 --> 01:02:14.521
Okay?

1040
01:02:35.962 --> 01:02:37.842
Come and have a look at this.

1041
01:02:40.716 --> 01:02:41.966
That is a miracle.

1042
01:02:42.093 --> 01:02:43.763
He's been sat there for about 15 minutes.

1043
01:03:01.737 --> 01:03:03.107
What's this, Dan?

1044
01:03:03.698 --> 01:03:04.738
It's a cassette.

1045
01:03:04.949 --> 01:03:06.119
What's a cassette?

1046
01:03:06.492 --> 01:03:08.122
Plays music. Come here, I'll show you.

1047
01:03:14.750 --> 01:03:15.790
All right.

1048
01:03:17.128 --> 01:03:20.208
You pop that in there.
Oh, no, you gotta take it out the case first.

1049
01:03:21.966 --> 01:03:23.376
It'll not play like that.

1050
01:03:24.427 --> 01:03:26.177
Right, you put that in there like that. Yeah?

1051
01:03:27.597 --> 01:03:28.927
And press that button there.

1052
01:03:31.893 --> 01:03:33.523
Bit more. Harder.

1053
01:03:34.020 --> 01:03:35.060
That's it.

1054
01:03:37.231 --> 01:03:38.321
It was Molly's.

1055
01:03:39.650 --> 01:03:40.990
She recorded it off the radio.

1056
01:03:41.777 --> 01:03:42.777
Shipping forecast.

1057
01:03:43.154 --> 01:03:44.784
It's on late at night.

1058
01:03:45.448 --> 01:03:48.488
Sailing By. D'you like that tune?

1059
01:03:48.618 --> 01:03:50.748
- Yeah.
- Yeah, Molly loved it.

1060
01:03:57.793 --> 01:03:59.173
It's nice, isn't it?

1061
01:04:11.224 --> 01:04:12.434
So how'd the interview go?

1062
01:04:12.808 --> 01:04:15.388
Oh, nothing's working out
with the school times at the minute.

1063
01:04:15.811 --> 01:04:18.811
So I went to, erm, some of the agencies
and put my name down on the waiting list,

1064
01:04:19.232 --> 01:04:20.822
cos I could do cleaning in the morning.

1065
01:04:21.150 --> 01:04:23.820
Went to some hotels.
Went round all the cafes.

1066
01:04:24.153 --> 01:04:25.573
Must have walked for bloody miles.

1067
01:04:25.821 --> 01:04:27.491
Well, I can pick the kids
up for you, you know.

1068
01:04:27.823 --> 01:04:29.033
Till I start work again.

1069
01:04:35.706 --> 01:04:38.206
Dan. The answer is "coconuts".

1070
01:04:38.960 --> 01:04:40.960
Correct.

1071
01:04:41.504 --> 01:04:42.844
What's he talking about, "coconuts"?

1072
01:04:43.214 --> 01:04:45.054
Ah, shall we tell your mum?

1073
01:04:46.008 --> 01:04:50.428
- Go on.
- When I was bouncing my ball on the stairs.

1074
01:04:50.846 --> 01:04:52.766
- What stairs?
- The stairs in our house.

1075
01:04:52.848 --> 01:04:55.728
- Yeah.
- Dan asked me a question.

1076
01:04:55.851 --> 01:04:57.441
What, what question did he ask ya?

1077
01:04:57.853 --> 01:04:59.693
"What kills people more?

1078
01:04:59.855 --> 01:05:01.777
- "Coconuts or sharks?"
- Mmm-hmm.

1079
01:05:01.857 --> 01:05:03.187
And I said coconuts.

1080
01:05:03.317 --> 01:05:04.357
And you got it right?

1081
01:05:04.485 --> 01:05:05.855
- Is that right?
- Yeah, he's right.

1082
01:05:11.659 --> 01:05:12.699
Is that Molly?

1083
01:05:14.870 --> 01:05:16.410
Yeah. Yeah, that's Molly, yeah.

1084
01:05:17.415 --> 01:05:18.865
Let's see that, Dais.

1085
01:05:19.750 --> 01:05:20.880
Show me that one.

1086
01:05:25.339 --> 01:05:27.299
"Molly." Like the name.

1087
01:05:28.050 --> 01:05:29.640
What was she like?

1088
01:05:30.886 --> 01:05:31.926
She was special.

1089
01:05:33.097 --> 01:05:35.677
Yeah, she was special, Daisy.

1090
01:05:37.143 --> 01:05:38.523
Not easy.

1091
01:05:40.563 --> 01:05:42.273
She was up one minute, down the next.

1092
01:05:44.692 --> 01:05:46.902
Smart and funny. Huh.

1093
01:05:48.738 --> 01:05:50.908
Ah, that lass made me laugh.

1094
01:05:52.908 --> 01:05:54.078
Kind.

1095
01:05:55.870 --> 01:05:57.040
She had a big, big heart.

1096
01:05:58.914 --> 01:05:59.924
But...

1097
01:06:01.917 --> 01:06:04.377
She said her head was like the ocean.

1098
01:06:06.922 --> 01:06:09.092
Dead still, then wild.

1099
01:06:11.385 --> 01:06:12.925
Never knew where she'd end up next.

1100
01:06:14.764 --> 01:06:16.354
I mean, the music helped that.

1101
01:06:17.933 --> 01:06:19.693
But then she'd hit the rocks.

1102
01:06:20.353 --> 01:06:22.363
"Where'll we sail to tonight, Dan?"

1103
01:06:22.938 --> 01:06:24.398
That was our little joke.

1104
01:06:25.900 --> 01:06:27.190
Her last words to me were,

1105
01:06:29.904 --> 01:06:33.994
"I wanna sail away, Dan,
with the wind at me back.

1106
01:06:35.951 --> 01:06:37.121
"That's all I need, Dan."

1107
01:06:39.914 --> 01:06:41.084
Do you have any children?

1108
01:06:42.958 --> 01:06:45.128
I'd have loved that, Daisy. No.

1109
01:06:46.504 --> 01:06:48.344
- Do you miss her?
- Dais.

1110
01:06:48.756 --> 01:06:50.086
It's okay.

1111
01:06:51.926 --> 01:06:52.966
She was crazy.

1112
01:06:54.553 --> 01:06:55.763
Hard work.

1113
01:06:58.974 --> 01:07:00.234
But I loved her to bits.

1114
01:07:02.978 --> 01:07:04.648
I'm lost without her, really.

1115
01:07:08.984 --> 01:07:10.404
- There you go, pet.
- Oh, thank you.

1116
01:07:11.445 --> 01:07:12.985
That must have been hard for you, Dan.

1117
01:07:13.239 --> 01:07:14.989
I mean, did you look after her
right till the end?

1118
01:07:16.575 --> 01:07:19.995
Well, you know, I thought it'd be
a relief when she passed away.

1119
01:07:20.329 --> 01:07:24.039
Cos it was difficult to go into work,
you know, when she was ill.

1120
01:07:25.126 --> 01:07:28.166
And after you've been looking after
somebody for so long...

1121
01:07:29.046 --> 01:07:30.756
It seems to take over your life, you know.

1122
01:07:31.173 --> 01:07:32.973
- Yeah, and you forget your own.
- Huh.

1123
01:07:34.844 --> 01:07:36.394
Well she was lucky to have you.

1124
01:07:38.139 --> 01:07:41.769
Daisy's dad, I thought was
something really special.

1125
01:07:43.018 --> 01:07:44.228
He turned out not to be.

1126
01:07:45.020 --> 01:07:47.980
Me mum tried to warn me about it,
but I was 18, so I didn't listen.

1127
01:07:49.024 --> 01:07:51.034
And then I did the same
thing with Dylan's dad.

1128
01:07:52.611 --> 01:07:54.611
You're a young lass,
you got your whole life ahead of you.

1129
01:07:55.573 --> 01:07:58.033
And when you get back
to those books, you'll be flying.

1130
01:07:59.034 --> 01:08:01.164
Yeah, I can't look at 'em, Dan.
They really upset me.

1131
01:08:03.998 --> 01:08:06.038
- You gotta keep a hold, you know.
- Mmm-hmm.

1132
01:08:06.917 --> 01:08:08.287
You're doing your kids proud.

1133
01:08:12.173 --> 01:08:16.053
I mean, we all need the wind
at our back every now and then.

1134
01:08:16.469 --> 01:08:18.719
- Don't we?
- Mmm. Yeah.

1135
01:08:29.398 --> 01:08:31.108
Well that's not good enough, Mr Blake.

1136
01:08:32.651 --> 01:08:36.491
And how do I know you've actually
been in contact with all these employers?

1137
01:08:37.198 --> 01:08:40.698
Well, I walked round the town.
I gave out me CV by hand.

1138
01:08:41.619 --> 01:08:42.949
Well, prove it.

1139
01:08:43.287 --> 01:08:45.747
- How?
- Well, did you get a receipt?

1140
01:08:46.040 --> 01:08:47.500
Take a picture with your mobile?

1141
01:08:49.084 --> 01:08:50.094
With this?

1142
01:08:51.086 --> 01:08:52.586
I give you my word that's what I did.

1143
01:08:52.838 --> 01:08:54.418
That's not good enough, Mr Blake.

1144
01:08:55.257 --> 01:08:58.007
What about the Universal Job Match online?

1145
01:08:58.886 --> 01:09:02.096
I went to the library,
there's my appointment card.

1146
01:09:05.226 --> 01:09:08.396
Did my head in. And I tried my best.

1147
01:09:09.688 --> 01:09:11.108
It's not good enough.

1148
01:09:12.107 --> 01:09:13.817
Can I look at your CV?

1149
01:09:14.193 --> 01:09:15.243
All right.

1150
01:09:26.497 --> 01:09:29.117
Did you not learn anything
at the CV workshop?

1151
01:09:29.416 --> 01:09:30.956
You'd be surprised.

1152
01:09:33.128 --> 01:09:34.758
Not good enough, Sheila?

1153
01:09:37.132 --> 01:09:38.512
I'm afraid I'm gonna have to refer you

1154
01:09:38.634 --> 01:09:42.144
to a decision maker for a possible
sanction for four weeks.

1155
01:09:43.347 --> 01:09:45.427
Your payment will be frozen.

1156
01:09:46.141 --> 01:09:48.691
You may be entitled
to Hardship Allowance if you apply.

1157
01:09:49.562 --> 01:09:50.982
Do you understand?

1158
01:09:52.147 --> 01:09:56.317
And if you are sanctioned, you must
continue to look for work and sign on.

1159
01:09:56.443 --> 01:09:59.363
If you don't, you may be sanctioned again.

1160
01:09:59.905 --> 01:10:04.155
And it's likely to be for thirteen weeks
on the second occasion, and thereafter.

1161
01:10:04.451 --> 01:10:08.751
And likely to be the maximum
of up to three years.

1162
01:10:09.915 --> 01:10:13.165
Would you like me to write
you a referral to a food bank?

1163
01:10:46.160 --> 01:10:47.910
Dan, you're not leaving, are you?

1164
01:10:48.203 --> 01:10:49.623
Aye, I'm off to the Bahamas.

1165
01:10:50.956 --> 01:10:53.206
Nah, I'm just sick of the old stuff.
I need a change.

1166
01:10:54.376 --> 01:10:55.586
Are you okay, Dan?

1167
01:10:56.962 --> 01:10:58.012
I'm fine, son.

1168
01:10:58.380 --> 01:11:00.010
You don't look okay.

1169
01:11:00.299 --> 01:11:01.629
No, really, I'm fine.

1170
01:11:02.426 --> 01:11:04.926
You haven't given us a row
about leaving the rubbish out.

1171
01:11:05.971 --> 01:11:07.351
I'm okay, China, really.

1172
01:11:09.016 --> 01:11:10.596
If you need anything, Dan, let me know.

1173
01:11:11.060 --> 01:11:12.230
Absolutely anything.

1174
01:11:15.230 --> 01:11:17.020
I mean it, Dan, anything.

1175
01:11:17.441 --> 01:11:18.821
I know, son.

1176
01:11:20.527 --> 01:11:23.527
Twenty, forty, sixty, eighty, a hundred.

